The paper proposes a deep learning framework for vessel monitoring using AIS data streams, which involves addressing issues such as massive amount of streaming data, noisy data, and irregular time-sampling. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories, as well as the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computer Vision (cs.CV), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories, which are all relevant to the proposed framework.
